{
  "stem": "4189.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "As it turned out it was a very good scheme, because when we got to the border and the-- the border patrol came, the passport control came on the train to ask for passports, we, of course, had no passports and we had no Visas to go.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And you have to remember, though, that we were both two young children.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was 14, my brother was 11.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So when the passport control asked us for our Visas, we just showed them our ticket to Paris, return ticket to Paris, and we showed them our identity cards which was marked with a large red J to indicate that we were Jews.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So the border patrol looked at those papers, there were two of them.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And one said to the other, well, they're going to Paris.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Let the French worry about them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So that's how we go through the border.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We got into Brussels, my uncle was waiting there with my aunt at the station, and they took us off the train, and we went with him to Antwerp where he was living in a rooming house.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the lady at-- at the rooming house had another room available upstairs underneath the roof, like what they call a [NON-ENGLISH], they called it over there.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It's a room right under the roof.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they gave that to us and we stayed there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now my mother, of course, she could not do this because a grown up, an adult, could never pass that scheme, but we did.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So she was supposed to go to Aachen.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Aachen is the last town from Germany to Belgium on the border.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That's right on the boarder of Belgium.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
